From cou.: 7 Subsequently, diffusion equations are linearised using the finite difference approach. By this means, we obtain a system of equations that is then solved using the n-dimensional Newton method. At each iteration step, the Newton correction vector is calculated through Gauss elimination and triagonal matrix decomposition.
From Soup: 7 Subsequently, diffusion equations are linearised using the finite difference approach. By this means, we obtain a system of equations that is then solved using the n -dimensional Newton method. At each iteration step, the Newton correction vector is calculated through Gauss elimination and triagonal matrix decomposition.
