From cou.: 9 As it is common practise in electrochemical simulations and for reasons of practicability, results are computed in dimensionless coordinates and then transformed into SI units (a detailed discussion can be found in18). Even though test procedures can equally be used in any system of units, it is advantageous to include the transformations into the finally used unit system in the testing process in order to cover all possible sources of errors. A list of all employed variables and their transformations can be found in Tables 1 and 2.
