From Soup: 57 Once all relevant parameters are identified, they can be are varied while the accuracy of computed results is monitored. As the computational workload is usually a function of these parameters, convergence studies often result in trade-off situations between the accuracy of simulation results and the required computation time, which must be solved through an exact definition of the necessary accuracy.
